   <mods:abstract>Mrs. Morris was happy to learn that the Jays have left Spain for France.
            Although she has not received a line from either of them, she has spoken to people who
            have seen the Jays. She was glad to hear of their rapid recoveries from indispositions
            suffered. If it were not for the impossibility of seeing Mrs. Jay and the possibility of
            preferring an assumed form to her own, Mrs. Morris thinks it might be fun to "occupy
            each others bodys to prevent any Derangement that might happen in our familys" in order
            that she might visit Paris and Sally might spend a few days in the United States. Kitty
            is with the Morrises, and looks much better since her recovery from an illness. Kitty
            has decided to spend the rest of the winter in New Jersey.</mods:abstract>
